article.description: Chase Edmonds rushed for 359 yards and four touchdowns, Kevin Anderson passed for three scores and ran for another, and Fordham set a school single-game rushing record with 516 yards in beating L
article.headline: Fordham sets rushing record in 58-34 win over Lafayette
article.linkText: Fordham sets rushing record in 58-34 win over Lafayette
article.story: NEW YORK -- Chase Edmonds rushed for 359 yards and four touchdowns, Kevin Anderson passed for three scores and ran for another, and Fordham set a school single-game rushing record with 516 yards in beating Lafayette 58-34 on Saturday. Edmonds broke his own school record of 348 yards, and scored on runs of 29, 19, 74 and 67 yards. The Rams (3-2, 1-0 Patriot League) had 709 yards of total offense, with Anderson completing 12 of 18 passes for 181 yards and rushing for 108 yards on 10 carries, including a 33-yard TD run. Anderson hit Corey Caddle with an 11-yard TD pass and Robbie Cantelli on a 22-yarder to help Fordham build a 41-20 halftime lead. Blake Searfoss was 25 of 41 for 325 yards passing for Lafayette (1-5, 0-2), with a 65-yard TD pass to Joey Chenoweth. Searfoss also scored on a 7-yard run and DeSean Brown had a 6-yard TD run.
